The system was designed and implemented by me, with code inspired by Swayam and supported by his assistance in debugging and improvements.
We focused on the physical build of the spider robot. We connected all 8 servo motors to the PCA9685 PWM driver and wired the PCA9685 to the ESP32 via I2C (SDA → GPIO 21, SCL → GPIO 22). A big thanks to Swayam who helped with connecting and organising the servo motor wiring to the correct channels on the PCA9685. We also began testing individual servo movement using MicroPython in Thonny to verify each channel was responding correctly before moving on to the full walking code.
